{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01WJjJH7u8dFa7ZmVk4zyjZ2","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The cluster is fully operational. Here's a summary of what was wrong and how it was fixed:\n\n**Root cause:** The StatefulSet command hardcoded `default.svc.cluster.local` in both `--advertise-host` and `--join` flags, but the pods live in the `cockroachdb` namespace. DNS resolution for `crdb-cluster-1.crdb-cluster.default.svc.cluster.local` fails because the correct domain is `crdb-cluster-1.crdb-cluster.cockroachdb.svc.cluster.local`.\n\n**Fix:**\n1. Patched the StatefulSet to replace `default` with `cockroachdb` in all three addresses.\n2. Deleted all 3 pods simultaneously (forced by the rolling-update deadlock — pods can't become Ready until init, but init needs all nodes to resolve each other).\n3. Ran `cockroach init --insecure` once all nodes were communicating correctly.\n\n**Result:** 3/3 nodes healthy (`is_available=true`, `is_live=true`), SQL connections accepted."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":335,"cache_read_input_tokens":43404,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":335},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"99c67227-c87d-4eca-b2e1-e9d43c281e79","uuid":"44d93fa2-c778-4a88-b86d-fb7ef77323ea","request_id":"req_011Cc5EBsCz5bHAxrzPZdomb"}
